From Sharon Paulson Subject food related seizures I am posting to this group in hopes of finding someone out there in network newsland who has heard of something similar to what I am going to describe I have a fourteen year old daugter who experienced a seizure on November at after eating Kellog's Frosted She is perfectly healthy had never experienced anything like this before and there is no history of seizures in either side of the All the tests EEG MRI EKG came out negative so the decision was made to do nothing and just wait to see if it happened Well we were going along fine and the other morning April she had a bowl of another Kellog's frosted kind of cereal Fruit Loops I am embarrassed to admit that I even bought that junk but every once in a So I pour it in her bowl and think Oh oh this is the same kind of junk she was eating when she had that Ten minutes later she had a full blown This was her first exposure to a sugar coated cereal since the last When I mentioned what she ate the first time as a possible reason for the seizure the neurologist basically negated that as an Now after this second episode so similar in nature to the first even he is scratching his Once again her EEG looks normal which I understand can happen even when a person has a Once again we are I have been thinking that it would be good to get to as large a group as possible to see if anyone has any experience with this kind of I know that members of the medical community are sometimes loathe to admit the importance that diet and foods play in our general health and well Anyway as you can guess I am worried sick about this and would appreciate any ideas anyone out there Sorry to be so wordy but I wanted to really get across what is going on Sharon Paulson NASA Langley Research Center Mailstop Work Hampton Home